<p>The <a href="https://ppesociety.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Philosophy, Politics, and Economics Society</a>Â is the recipient of a $3.2 million award.<span id="more-54544"></span></p>
<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-54545 aligncenter" src="https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/ppe-society-dollar-bill.jpg" alt="" width="559" height="339" srcset="https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/ppe-society-dollar-bill.jpg 559w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/ppe-society-dollar-bill-300x182.jpg 300w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/ppe-society-dollar-bill-400x243.jpg 400w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 559px) 100vw, 559px" /></p>
<p>The funds, from the <a href="https://www.templeton.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">John Templeton Foundation</a>, will &#8220;establish an international grant initiative to support PPE research projects, host workshops for the award winners, and build an expansive catalog of research and teaching resources,&#8221; the PPE Society announced. The grant initiative &#8220;will primarily offer funding for teams of PPE scholars working together to address areas of pressing importance that call for, and will benefit substantially from, PPE research,&#8221; according to the Society&#8217;s website.</p>
<p>The Philosophy, Politics, and Economics Society is based at the University of North Carolina, Chapel Hill, and is directed by professor of philosophy <a href="https://philosophy.unc.edu/people/geoffrey-sayre-mccord/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Geoffrey Sayre-McCord</a>.</p>
<p>More information about the society&#8217;s research consortium and plans can be found <a href="https://ppesociety.org/the-philosophy-politics-and-economics-ppe-research-consortium/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">here</a>.</p>
